mem:fact-01kje30pfdnvpv5fx0ng4234jf a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "The `docs/` directory is the canonical documentation source of truth, containing 15 sections and ~124 markdown files. It is designed for future static-site generators (mdBook, Zola, Docusaurus) and renders natively on GitHub.\n\n**Navigation & discovery:**\n- `docs/SUMMARY.md` is the **table of contents** — a hierarchical list of every page. When adding a new doc, always add its entry here.\n- Each subdirectory has a `README.md` that acts as a **hub page** listing all docs in that section with brief descriptions. When adding a doc to a section, update that section's README too.\n- The top-level `docs/README.md` is a short meta-doc explaining authoring conventions (one topic per file, capability-based names, relative links).\n\n**Section layout:**\n| Section | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cli/` | One file per CLI command (init, create, query, etc.) |\n| `getting-started/` | Quickstart guides (server, ledger, write, query, Rust API) |\n| `concepts/` | Core concepts (ledgers, IRIs, datatypes, datasets, time-travel, policy) |\n| `design/` | Deep-dive architecture docs (query execution, index format, storage traits, nameservice, commits) |\n| `api/` | HTTP API (endpoints, headers, signed requests, errors) |\n| `query/` | Query guides (JSON-LD, SPARQL, output formats, datasets, CONSTRUCT, explain) |\n| `transactions/` | Transaction guides (insert, upsert, update/delete, retractions, turtle, signing) |\n| `security/` | Auth, encryption, commit signing, policy model |\n| `indexing-and-search/` | Indexing, reindex, fulltext, BM25, vector, geospatial |\n| `graph-sources/` | External graph sources (Iceberg, R2RML, BM25) |\n| `operations/` | Config, storage backends, DynamoDB, telemetry, admin/health |\n| `troubleshooting/` | Common errors, debugging queries, performance tracing |\n| `reference/` | Glossary, vocabulary, crate-map, connection config, compatibility |\n| `contributing/` | Dev setup, tests, SPARQL compliance, tracing guide, design notes |\n\n**Where to put new content:**\n- **New CLI command** → `docs/cli/<command>.md` + entry in SUMMARY.md\n- **New concept or behavior explanation** → `docs/concepts/` or the most relevant existing section\n- **New internal architecture/design decision** → `docs/design/`\n- **New operational guide (config, deployment)** → `docs/operations/`\n- **New troubleshooting entry** → `docs/troubleshooting/`\n- **New reference material (glossary term, crate)** → `docs/reference/`\n- **Entirely new section** → create subdir with README.md hub, add to SUMMARY.md\n\n**Authoring conventions:**\n- One topic per file; use stable capability-based names (e.g., `sparql.md` not `sparql-v1.1.md`)\n- Use relative links within docs/ (e.g., `../concepts/time-travel.md`)\n- Structure: Title → Overview → Subtopics → Code examples → Related docs / See also\n- Include bash/JSON/SPARQL code blocks for examples\n- `docs/contributing/README.md` is the detailed contributor guide (372 lines) covering style, PR format, and workflow — it is NOT just a hub page like other section READMEs." ;
    mem:tag "README" ;
    mem:tag "SUMMARY.md" ;
    mem:tag "authoring" ;
    mem:tag "contributing" ;
    mem:tag "docs" ;
    mem:tag "documentation" ;
    mem:tag "project-structure" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/README.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/SUMMARY.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/contributing/README.md" ;
    mem:branch "feature/config-graph" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-26T23:02:20.397376+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjg3zmevnz6mdn53wkqn08p0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fluree uses CIDv1 (Content Identifier v1) for all content-addressed blobs. Implementation is in fluree-db-core/src/content_id.rs wrapping the `cid` crate's `Cid` struct.\n\n**Format:** CIDv1 = version(1) + multicodec + multihash(SHA2-256, 32 bytes)\n\n**Multicodec values** (private-use range 0x300000+, defined in fluree-db-core/src/content_kind.rs):\n- 0x300001 Commit, 0x300002 Txn, 0x300003 IndexRoot, 0x300004 IndexBranch, 0x300005 IndexLeaf\n- 0x300006 DictBlob, 0x300007 Garbage, 0x300008 LedgerConfig, 0x300009 StatsSketch\n- 0x30000A GraphSourceSnapshot, 0x30000B SpatialIndex\n\n**Key APIs:**\n- `ContentId::new(kind, bytes)` — hashes bytes with SHA-256, tags with Fluree multicodec\n- `ContentId::verify(bytes)` — re-hashes and compares (NOT valid for commit-v2 blobs which exclude trailing hash+sig)\n- `ContentId::digest_hex()` — 64-char hex SHA-256 hash string\n- `ContentId::codec()` — returns the multicodec u64 value\n- Display uses base32-lower multibase encoding (produces `bafy...`/`bafk...` prefixes)\n- `from_codec(u64) -> Option<ContentKind>` reverse mapping\n\n**ContentKind enum** maps each blob type to its codec. `DictBlob { dict: DictKind }` sub-kinds all share one codec (0x300006); the dict sub-kind is in the stored bytes, not the CID.\n\n**Crate dependencies:** `cid = \"0.11\"`, `multihash = \"0.19\"`, `sha2 = \"0.10\"`" ;
    mem:tag "CIDv1" ;
    mem:tag "SHA-256" ;
    mem:tag "architecture" ;
    mem:tag "content-id" ;
    mem:tag "content-kind" ;
    mem:tag "multicodec" ;
    mem:tag "multihash" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/content_id.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/content_kind.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/ipfs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-27T17:57:43.003928+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjj80gw99c7hp8qh0tfp60kg a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "IPFS storage backend (fluree-db-storage-ipfs crate) — full implementation details:\n\n**Crate structure:**\n- `src/lib.rs` — IpfsStorage struct implementing ContentStore + full Storage trait (StorageRead, StorageWrite, ContentAddressedWrite, StorageMethod)\n- `src/kubo.rs` — Thin HTTP RPC client for Kubo (block/put, block/get, block/stat, pin/add, pin/rm, is_pinned, id). Uses `reqwest` with multipart form upload.\n- `src/address.rs` — Parses `fluree:ipfs://ledger/kind/{hash}.ext` addresses. `extract_hash_hex()` gets the 64-char SHA-256 hex from the filename stem. `hash_hex_to_cid_string()` constructs a raw-codec CIDv1 for retrieval.\n- `src/error.rs` — IpfsStorageError enum (ConnectionFailed, NotFound, Rpc, Http, CidMismatch, Other). Implements `From<IpfsStorageError> for fluree_db_core::error::Error`.\n- `tests/it_kubo_block_api.rs` — 8 integration tests gated behind `integration-tests` feature. Require running Kubo at localhost:5001.\n\n**Kubo codec/pin behavior (verified by integration tests):**\n- `block/put` with Fluree's private-use multicodec (e.g. `cid-codec=0x300001`) — Kubo ACCEPTS it, stores the block, returns a CID with that codec\n- `block/get` with cross-codec CID — Kubo resolves by multihash regardless of codec, so a raw-codec CID retrieves blocks stored with any Fluree codec\n- `pin/add` with Fluree-codec CID — Kubo REJECTS it (\"no decoder registered for multicodec code 0x300001\") because pin/add tries to decode the block for DAG traversal\n- **Workaround:** pin using a raw-codec (0x55) CID built from the same SHA-256 multihash. `IpfsStorage::to_raw_cid()` and `address::hash_hex_to_cid_string()` handle this. Same approach for pin/rm (unpin).\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- `put()` stores with Fluree's native multicodec — preserves CID identity in IPFS\n- Retrieval uses raw-codec CID constructed from address hash hex\n- `delete()` is a no-op (IPFS is immutable; GC via unpin)\n- `list_prefix()` returns error — NOT needed because: (1) nameservice always runs locally (file/DynamoDB) and handles all_records/all_graph_source_records, (2) drop_ledger Hard mode should walk commit chain + index chain + tree structure to discover CIDs rather than listing by prefix (existing code: walk_commit_chain_full, walk_prev_index_chain, clean_garbage, load_from_root_v5)\n\n**Feature flag chain:** cli/ipfs → server/ipfs → api/ipfs → connection/ipfs → dep:fluree-db-storage-ipfs\n\n**Connection config:**\n- JSON-LD: `ipfsApiUrl` and `ipfsPinOnPut` fields on Storage node (vocab constants in fluree-db-connection/src/vocab.rs)\n- Flat JSON: `@type: \"IpfsStorage\"` with `ipfsApiUrl`/`ipfsPinOnPut` fields\n- IpfsStorageConfig struct in fluree-db-connection/src/config.rs\n- IpfsConnection type alias and connect_ipfs factory in fluree-db-connection/src/ipfs.rs\n\n**Documentation:** docs/operations/ipfs-storage.md (comprehensive guide), updates to storage.md, connection-config-jsonld.md, SUMMARY.md" ;
    mem:tag "CID" ;
    mem:tag "IPFS" ;
    mem:tag "architecture" ;
    mem:tag "codec" ;
    mem:tag "connection" ;
    mem:tag "feature-flags" ;
    mem:tag "integration-tests" ;
    mem:tag "kubo" ;
    mem:tag "pinning" ;
    mem:tag "storage" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/operations/ipfs-storage.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-connection/src/config.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-connection/src/ipfs.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-storage-ipfs/src/address.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-storage-ipfs/src/error.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-storage-ipfs/src/kubo.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-storage-ipfs/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-storage-ipfs/tests/it_kubo_block_api.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/ipfs" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01kjg407n8cqjy24njyyhz6dnz ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T13:46:35.273059+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjjd0b982vvxq7kxvn9bs90s a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Historical time-travel views must attach a BinaryRangeProvider when loading a BinaryIndexStore. `LedgerSnapshot::from_root_bytes()` produces a metadata-only snapshot with `range_provider=None`, so `Fluree::load_graph_db_at_t()` needs to set `LedgerSnapshot.range_provider = Some(BinaryRangeProvider::new(store, dict_novelty))` after loading the binary store; otherwise range-based operators can error with: \"binary-only db has no range_provider attached — load and attach BinaryIndexStore before queries\"." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "binaryrangeprovider" ;
    mem:tag "bugfix" ;
    mem:tag "historical-view" ;
    mem:tag "range-provider" ;
    mem:tag "time-travel" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/fluree_ext.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/db.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/range.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T15:13:52.424054+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjjmk1nva80w5cj3ey87asnj a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Global LRU \"leaflet cache\" (single memory budget):\n- Implementation: `fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs` (`LeafletCache`) uses a single `moka::sync::Cache` (TinyLFU) shared across decoded entry types (R1/R2 leaflet regions + dict leaves + BM25 leaflets + vector shards). One pool = one cache budget.\n- Budget control: `FLUREE_LEAFLET_CACHE_BYTES` (default 8 GiB) sets the max bytes for the cache.\n- Wiring: enabled by default in `fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs` (`LedgerManagerConfig::default()` creates `LeafletCache::with_max_bytes(...)`), and used by `BinaryIndexStore` load paths when ledger caching is on.\n- Note: Region 3 (history journal) is intentionally never cached (cold path)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet-cache" ;
    mem:tag "lru" ;
    mem:tag "moka" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T17:26:25.211748+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjjn8kspr3gnkcsmq9t1fsvf a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "API-level ledger-info caching (for upstream apps):\n- Location: `fluree-db-api/src/ledger_info.rs` (`LedgerInfoBuilder::execute`).\n- Cache backend: the global unified `LeafletCache` (TinyLFU) so ledger-info shares the single memory budget with other cached decode artifacts.\n- Budget control: `FLUREE_LEAFLET_CACHE_BYTES` (default 8 GiB).\n- Key: xxh3_128 hash of a canonical string including (ledger_id, commit_t=ledger.t(), index_t=ledger.snapshot.t, realtime_property_details, include_property_datatypes, graph selector, context JSON hash).\n- Value: serialized JSON bytes (`Arc<[u8]>`) stored in `fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs` under a new `LedgerInfo` entry type.\n- Behavior: cache hit returns parsed JSON without recomputing novelty-merged stats; cache naturally busts when commit_t or index_t changes." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet-cache" ;
    mem:tag "ledger-info" ;
    mem:tag "moka" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "tinylfu" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_info.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T17:38:11.894884+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kjjswkfg62ratezvpdchg30h a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Leaflet region decode behavior (read-side): `BinaryCursor` decodes Region 1 first and only decodes Region 2 (dt/t/lang/i) when (a) the caller requested metadata via `need_region2` AND there is at least one Region-1 match in that leaflet, OR (b) overlay merge is active, OR (c) time-travel replay is active. Region 1 and Region 2 are cached independently in the unified `LeafletCache` (TinyLFU) so caching R1 does not imply caching R2. Region 3 (history journal) is decoded only for time-travel and is intentionally never cached; however leaf files are currently fetched/mmap'd as whole objects, so Region 3 bytes still contribute to leaf download size for non-history queries." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "region1" ;
    mem:tag "region2" ;
    mem:tag "region3" ;
    mem:tag "time-travel" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/format/leaflet.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_cursor.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/leaflet_cache.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-02-28T18:59:01.232091+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjp8g2s9pfh64sbx1crx42d8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Query API layering in fluree-db-api:\n- `Fluree::query_connection(...)` is the request-boundary entrypoint. It parses dataset spec/options from the query itself, chooses the execution model, and applies per-source/global policy and config-graph defaults. It uses GraphDb for single-ledger (including time travel via spec) and DataSetDb for multi-ledger union.\n- `Fluree::query(&GraphDb, ...)` is the stable single-ledger \"db is a value\" API. You load a `GraphDb` once via `db() / db_at_t() / db_at()` (supports `#txn-meta` / named graph selection) and then run many queries with uniform wrapper behavior (policy/reasoning/config).\n- `DataSetDb` supports a Fluree history/changes mode via `history_range: Option<(from_t,to_t)>`; dataset execution threads `history_mode`, `from_t`, and `to_t` into the query engine (`ContextConfig`) enabling time-range / @op semantics." ;
    mem:tag "api-layering" ;
    mem:tag "dataset" ;
    mem:tag "fluree-db-api" ;
    mem:tag "graphdb" ;
    mem:tag "history" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "query-connection" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/query/connection.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/dataset_query.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/fluree_ext.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/view/query.rs" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01kjn63vy23w6kehy3gbs30ncv ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-02T03:12:02.857222+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "api" .

mem:fact-01kjt5bpzz5aqvv93syafs18m1 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fast GROUP BY ?o COUNT(?s) top-k optimization is now generic for any bound predicate in POST: `PredicateGroupCountFirstsOperator` scans leaflets using uncompressed per-leaflet FIRST (p,o) metadata and uses boundary-equality (FIRST(i)==FIRST(i+1)) to add `row_count` without decoding. It consults `StatsView::get_graph_property(g_id,p_id)` at open-time: if exactly one datatype and it maps to a reserved dt_id (and is not langString), it avoids decoding Region2 entirely and emits `EncodedLit` with constant dt_id/lang_id=0; otherwise it falls back to decoding Region2 and groups by (o_kind,o_key,dt_id,lang_id) for correctness." ;
    mem:tag "count" ;
    mem:tag "datatype" ;
    mem:tag "group-by" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
    mem:tag "optimization" ;
    mem:tag "post-index" ;
    mem:tag "region2" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "statsview" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/execute/operator_tree.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-03T15:34:11.711499+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kjtbbfnpgec8tk0zqjeg7sb8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Added POST leaflet-skipping fast path for bound-object COUNT queries: `PredicateObjectCountFirstsOperator` answers `SELECT (COUNT(?s) AS ?c) WHERE { ?s <p> <o> }` (single triple, bound predicate+object, no dt/lang constraint, no GROUP BY) by scanning POST leaflets using uncompressed FIRST (p,o) metadata and boundary-equality to add `row_count` without decoding; falls back to decoding Region1 for partial leaflets. Wired via `detect_predicate_object_count` in `execute/operator_tree.rs`, and preserves existing loose semantics when `tp.dtc` is None (ignores dt/lang)." ;
    mem:tag "count" ;
    mem:tag "fast-path" ;
    mem:tag "leaflet" ;
