mem:fact-01km06dhjzpgyvbs1yc5h0h28e a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Default context feature -- end-to-end architecture:\n\nWhat: Per-ledger JSON object mapping prefixes to IRIs (e.g. {\"ex\": \"http://example.org/\"}). Applied automatically to queries/transactions that omit their own @context.\n\nStorage: Context JSON blob lives in CAS (content-addressed storage) keyed by ContentId. The ContentId pointer is stored in ConfigPayload.default_context within the nameservice config (ConfigPublisher trait).\n\nPopulation paths:\n1. Bulk import (fluree create --from) -- store_default_context() in import.rs captures Turtle @prefix declarations + built-in prefixes and writes to CAS/nameservice\n2. API -- Fluree::set_default_context() in lib.rs (requires N: ConfigPublisher)\n3. HTTP -- PUT /v1/fluree/context/*ledger in routes/context.rs\n4. CLI -- fluree context set in commands/context_cmd.rs\n\nRead paths:\n1. Ledger loading -- ledger_manager.rs reads NsRecord.default_context CID, fetches blob from CAS, stores in LedgerState.default_context\n2. SPARQL query -- SparqlProcessor merges default context prefixes as fallback when query has no explicit PREFIX\n3. JSON-LD query -- default context merged when query omits @context\n4. API -- Fluree::get_default_context() reads config + CAS directly\n5. HTTP -- GET /v1/fluree/context/*ledger\n\nPrecedence: Query-level @context/PREFIX > ledger default context > built-in prefixes (rdf, rdfs, xsd, owl, sh, geo).\n\nConcurrency: Updates use CAS (compare-and-set) via ConfigPublisher::push_config() with retry loop (3 attempts). Backend-specific: S3 uses ETags, DynamoDB conditional expressions, File uses flock(), Memory uses parking_lot::RwLock.\n\nCache invalidation: After update, disconnect_ledger() evicts cached LedgerState so next query reloads with new context.\n\nProxy mode: ProxyNameService does NOT implement ConfigPublisher, so context writes are only available on the tx server. Proxy GET reads from cached LedgerState.default_context." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "cas" ;
    mem:tag "cli" ;
    mem:tag "default-context" ;
    mem:tag "http-endpoint" ;
    mem:tag "nameservice" ;
    mem:tag "prefix" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/api/endpoints.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/cli/context.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/concepts/iri-and-context.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/import.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-cli/src/commands/context_cmd.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-nameservice/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/src/routes/context.rs" ;
    mem:branch "feature/default-context" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-18T10:03:48.703812+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .


mem:fact-01km33dyv5wxhrxt4gnqra4xwb a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Ledger cache incremental refresh gotchas:\n- `LedgerState::apply_loaded_db(new_snapshot, ...)` replaces `snapshot` and trims `novelty` via `clear_up_to(new_snapshot.t)` but **does not reapply commit envelope deltas** (namespace_codes + graph_registry) for any remaining novelty commits with `t > new_snapshot.t`. If you keep novelty after an index advance, you must preserve/merge those deltas (or re-trace remaining commits) or queries/commit-apply may fail due to missing namespace prefixes / graph routing.\n- When wiring binary v2 index via `BinaryRangeProvider`, the provider's `DictNovelty` must be the same `state.dict_novelty` that is reset/populated after index application. Using `DictNovelty::new_uninitialized()` (or any detached Arc) can break overlay translation for subject/string IDs introduced in novelty.\n- Likewise, `BinaryIndexStore::augment_namespace_codes(&snapshot.namespace_codes)` is needed when novelty introduces new namespace codes not in the index root (prefix trie + decode correctness)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "caching" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "gotcha" ;
    mem:tag "graph-registry" ;
    mem:tag "indexing" ;
    mem:tag "ledger-manager" ;
    mem:tag "namespace" ;
    mem:tag "range-provider" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-core/src/db.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-ledger/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-19T13:09:19.845735+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01km4f8dv0jzt33vdww5k6gef0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Novelty-aware decoding consolidation (BinaryIndex V6/V3 query paths):\n- `BinaryGraphView` now carries `dict_novelty: Option<Arc<DictNovelty>>` and performs watermark routing internally for dict-backed types (IriRef, StringDict, JsonArena) in both `decode_value(o_type, ...)` and `decode_value_from_kind(o_kind, dt_id, lang_id, ...)`, plus `resolve_subject_iri`.\n- Added `BinaryGraphView::resolve_subject_sid(s_id)` and internal `resolve_novel_subject_sid()` so novelty subjects can return `Sid::new(ns_code, suffix)` directly (avoids IRI string concat + `encode_iri` trie lookup).\n- `ExecutionContext::graph_view()` should construct views via `BinaryIndexStore::graph_with_novelty(g_id, dict_novelty.clone())` so call sites become novelty-safe by default.\n- When decoding `Binding::EncodedLit`, always use `decode_value_from_kind(o_kind,o_key,p_id,dt_id,lang_id)` (dt_id is DatatypeDictId, not o_type; p_id needed for NUM_BIG arenas)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "binarygraphview" ;
    mem:tag "decode" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "novelty-aware" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "watermark" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/context.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/join.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T01:55:15.936809+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01km5nyf5803na09n60d6z8j30 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Binary-scan bound-term normalization depends on BinaryIndexStore namespace codes: `BinaryScanOperator::extract_bound_terms` re-encodes `Ref::Sid`/`Term::Sid` via `re_encode_sid`, which does `store.sid_to_iri(sid)` then `store.encode_iri(&iri)`. If the store lacks a namespace code (e.g., new namespace introduced in commits after the binary index was built/loaded), `sid_to_iri` drops the prefix (\"\" fallback) and `encode_iri` falls back to EMPTY (code 0), causing bound filters to miss and queries to return empty/incorrect results. Mitigation requires augmenting the BinaryIndexStore namespace table/prefix trie with the snapshot's `namespace_codes` whenever new namespace deltas are applied (or avoiding store-based re-encode when the store can't decode the Sid)." ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "namespace" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "prefix-trie" ;
    mem:tag "query-bug" ;
    mem:tag "reload" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger/loading.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_index_store.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-ledger/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T13:11:24.072938+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01km5pmwnsym5zz3vgpyz4k1rt a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Fix for 'new namespace after binary index attached' bound-query bug: `BinaryScanOperator` now keeps bound pattern SIDs in *snapshot* namespace space for overlay matching, and constructs persisted binary filters by decoding those SIDs to full IRIs via `LedgerSnapshot::decode_sid` then re-encoding via `BinaryIndexStore::encode_iri`. This avoids depending on the store's namespace table being updated after commit deltas, while preserving correct filtering when store namespace codes differ from snapshot (e.g., after rebuild). Regression test: `fluree-db-api/tests/it_namespace_new_after_index.rs`." ;
    mem:tag "binary-scan" ;
    mem:tag "namespace" ;
    mem:tag "novelty" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "prefix-trie" ;
    mem:tag "regression-test" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_namespace_new_after_index.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T13:23:38.809931+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01km6e7s84vcmvhrxvtcwgfkka a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "`IriCompactor` only auto-derives fallback prefixes when the provided `ParsedContext` is non-empty (has terms/@vocab/@base). If you want compact display IRIs without a user-supplied @context, pass a synthetic context with well-known prefixes so fallback derivation activates for user namespaces too (e.g., `IriCompactor::with_fallback_prefixes(namespace_codes)` pattern). Also ensure any emitted `@context` matches the exact prefixes actually used for compaction (handle collisions/unique suffixes)." ;
    mem:tag "api" ;
    mem:tag "commit-detail" ;
    mem:tag "context" ;
    mem:tag "iri-compaction" ;
    mem:tag "json-ld" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/iri.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_commit_builder.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-20T20:15:55.140833+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "api" .

mem:constraint-01km6xq65xn4dzghwnf4wc5ax6 a mem:Constraint ;
    mem:content "Overlay ops for `BinaryCursor` overlay merge must be (1) sorted by the cursor's `RunSortOrder` and (2) deduplicated by `FactKeyV3` before merging, otherwise duplicate ops for the same fact can cause duplicate outputs or incorrect suppression. Dedup should be deterministic: if multiple ops share the same `FactKeyV3` at the same max `t`, prefer `retract` over `assert` (final state = not present) to avoid nondeterminism from `sort_unstable` tie ordering." ;
    mem:tag "binary-cursor" ;
    mem:tag "binary-index" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dedup" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "sort" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:severity "must" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/binary_cursor.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-binary-index/src/read/types.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T00:46:28.541390+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:decision-01km88js2zfk0b5465psvc8c35 a mem:Decision ;
    mem:content "Fast-path PSOT cursor builders and dependent operators now prefer correctness-preserving fallback over hard failure when novelty overlay translation to V3 IDs fails. `build_psot_cursor_for_predicate` (and the group variant) returns `Ok(None)` if overlay flakes can't be translated (e.g., missing/stale DictNovelty or unsupported value types), and callers treat `None` as \"fast path unavailable\" and run their provided fallback operators instead of returning an internal error. This keeps the hot path unchanged when translation succeeds and avoids silently wrong results under novelty edge cases." ;
    mem:tag "binary-cursor" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "fallback" ;
    mem:tag "fast-path" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "psot" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_group_count_firsts.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_path_common.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_property_path_plus_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_transitive_path_plus_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/fast_union_star_count_all.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T13:15:32.831834+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:rationale "Database correctness must not depend on flawless overlay translation; when overlay cannot be mapped into binary ID space, the system should choose a slower correct path rather than erroring or producing partial results." ;
    mem:alternatives "Hard-fail the query on translation error; always disable fast paths whenever overlay is present" .

mem:fact-01km81d85z7rfdckve3wqwtszx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Graph crawl formatting (`fluree-db-api/src/format/graph_crawl.rs`) fetches subject properties via `GraphDbRef::range` (SPOT/POST), which goes through `BinaryRangeProvider` when a binary index is attached. In `binary_range_eq_v3`, overlay flake→V3 `OverlayOp` translation can fail (e.g., `DictNovelty` uninitialized so novelty-only strings/subjects aren't resolvable). Previously those overlay flakes were WARN-logged then DROPPED, which can make properties disappear when a translated retract suppresses the base row but the asserted novelty value fails translation. Fix: keep failed translations as raw `Flake`s and run a post-pass that merges raw overlay flakes with cursor output, resolves per-fact lifecycles (latest t wins; tie prefers retract), drops retracts, then applies RangeOptions." ;
    mem:tag "binary-range" ;
    mem:tag "correctness" ;
    mem:tag "dict-novelty" ;
    mem:tag "graph-crawl" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/format/graph_crawl.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_range.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_scan.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T11:10:11.647303+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01km8qdr8jp1zs8eh6tmq8jfdx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Graph crawl formatter currently only includes `@id` when `*` is used (or `@id` explicitly selected) at that crawl level. This drops identity for nested ref sub-selects like `{ \"schema:isBasedOn\": [\"schema:name\"] }`, producing `{ \"schema:name\": ... }` without `@id`. Added regression test `jsonld_graph_crawl_nested_subselect_includes_id` in `fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_jsonld_basic.rs` asserting nested ref objects always include `@id` even when selecting specific properties." ;
    mem:tag "@id" ;
    mem:tag "formatter" ;
    mem:tag "graph-crawl" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "regression-test" ;
    mem:tag "subselect" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T17:34:56.786195+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01km8qneeknvq50y6dvm459rne a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Graph crawl formatter previously only included `@id` when `*` was used (or `@id` explicitly selected) at that crawl level, which dropped identity for nested ref sub-selects like `{ \"schema:isBasedOn\": [\"schema:name\"] }`, producing `{ \"schema:name\": ... }` without `@id`.\n\nFix: `fluree-db-api/src/format/graph_crawl.rs` now always includes `@id` for nested expansions (`current_depth > 0`), while keeping root-level behavior unchanged unless `*` or explicit `@id` is requested.\n\nRegression test: `jsonld_graph_crawl_nested_subselect_includes_id` in `fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_jsonld_basic.rs` (was failing, now passes)." ;
    mem:tag "@id" ;
    mem:tag "formatter" ;
    mem:tag "graph-crawl" ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "regression-test" ;
    mem:tag "subselect" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01km8qdr8jp1zs8eh6tmq8jfdx ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-21T17:39:08.884534+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kmbj3527qd54y3whzjhwc4bg a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL UPDATE improved WHERE support: `fluree-db-sparql` UPDATE `Modify.where_clause` now uses full `GraphPattern` (same as SELECT) so UPDATE WHERE can include OPTIONAL/FILTER/UNION/VALUES/BIND/subselects+aggregates. In `fluree-db-transact`, SPARQL UPDATE lowering (`lower_sparql_update.rs`) now stores the parsed WHERE as `Txn.sparql_where: Option<SparqlWhereClause { prologue, pattern }>` and defers lowering until staging (`stage.rs`) using `fluree_db_sparql::lower_sparql` with the current `LedgerSnapshot` as encoder. `stage::execute_where` now executes either JSON-LD unresolved patterns or SPARQL-lowered patterns via the same query engine (`execute_where_with_overlay_at_strict`). Added tests: `fluree-db-server/tests/integration.rs` covers SPARQL UPDATE with subquery+MAX+BIND; `fluree-db-api/tests/it_transact_conditional.rs` covers JSON-LD update using subquery aggregate `(as (max ?n) ?m)` + bind." ;
    mem:tag "aggregate" ;
    mem:tag "bind" ;
    mem:tag "max" ;
    mem:tag "query-engine" ;
    mem:tag "sparql" ;
    mem:tag "stage" ;
    mem:tag "subquery" ;
    mem:tag "transact" ;
    mem:tag "update" ;
    mem:tag "where" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "docs/query/sparql.md" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_transact_conditional.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-server/tests/integration.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/ast/update.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/parse/query/update.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/validate/mod.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/ir.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/lower_sparql_update.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/stage.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-22T19:59:29.863846+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmgg192p7hnveqckgqxyakz7 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Iceberg Direct catalog flow: in server-side scan paths, create the S3 storage client once and share it (e.g., Arc<Storage>) with SendDirectCatalogClient; avoid moving the storage into the catalog client and then re-creating storage just to read metadata/manifests. Use Arc::clone(&storage) for the catalog and pass &*storage to planners/readers." ;
    mem:tag "aws" ;
    mem:tag "direct-catalog" ;
    mem:tag "gotcha" ;
    mem:tag "iceberg" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "s3" ;
    mem:tag "storage" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_source/r2rml.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-iceberg/src/catalog/direct.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-iceberg/src/catalog/mod.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-24T17:59:43.446602+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmqem54pfgjxjv6k2t2wtmwd a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Temporary `[DIAG][commit-t]` instrumentation for the remote commit-t debugging pass was added in `graph_commit_builder.rs`, `ledger_manager.rs`, `lib.rs::refresh`, `binary_range.rs`, and `peer/sync_task.rs`. It traces SSE/refresh ingress, cached snapshot composition, notify planning and commit catch-up, exact txn-meta POST `db:t` lookups, raw overlay probes, and binary range filter/overlay translation decisions so one deploy can isolate whether the miss is in cache refresh, graph routing, or range-provider filtering." ;
    mem:tag "binary-range" ;
    mem:tag "commit-t" ;
    mem:tag "diagnostics" ;
    mem:tag "ledger-manager" ;
    mem:tag "overlay" ;
    mem:tag "refresh" ;
    mem:tag "txn-meta" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/graph_commit_builder.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/ledger_manager.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/src/lib.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/binary_range.rs" ;
