    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmtcm1frjadepjjastrvmng8 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Boolean FILTER caching is now implemented at the shared expression layer instead of as a STRSTARTS-specific fast path. `Expression::eval_to_bool_non_strict()` calls `try_eval_cached_bool_predicate()` in `fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs`, which caches deterministic single-variable boolean predicates over late-materialized encoded bindings (`EncodedLit`, `EncodedSid`, `EncodedPid`) using a thread-local LRU keyed by `(BinaryIndexStore pointer, graph id, expression hash, encoded binding identity)`. The static gate is conservative: it only admits boolean predicate shapes such as comparisons, `IN`/`NOT IN`, string predicates (`CONTAINS`, `STRSTARTS`, `STRENDS`, `REGEX`), `LANGMATCHES`, `SAMETERM`, and logical compositions of those, while excluding volatile functions like `RAND`, `NOW`, UUID generation, fulltext, vector, geo, and custom functions." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "expression" ;
    mem:tag "filter" ;
    mem:tag "late-materialization" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "regex" ;
    mem:tag "strstarts" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/eval.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/string.rs" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01kmt74hw9mt6dpzyxbrpnemmv ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T14:12:28.280119+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmtec88erhp5fk1f4gfybyp0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Boolean FILTER caching now hooks into strict `Expression::eval_to_bool()` rather than only `eval_to_bool_non_strict()`. `fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs::eval_cached_bool_predicate()` accepts a closure for uncached strict evaluation, and `fluree-db-query/src/expression/eval.rs` routes `eval_to_bool()` through that helper before falling back to `eval_to_bool_uncached()`. This means nested boolean conditions inside `IF`, `AND`, `OR`, and `NOT` automatically benefit from the same cache, while `eval_to_bool_non_strict()` preserves its demotion behavior by delegating to strict evaluation first and only demoting errors afterward." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "expression" ;
    mem:tag "filter" ;
    mem:tag "if" ;
    mem:tag "logical" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "strict-semantics" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/eval.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01kmtcm1frjadepjjastrvmng8 ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T14:43:10.222971+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmtepx0kz4nmz1sb455wxj2y a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Boolean expression caching now uses a single recursive analysis in `fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs` to derive cacheability, the single encoded input variable, and the expression hash in one traversal. The old separate recursive passes (`expr_returns_cacheable_bool`, `expr_may_materialize_encoded_value`, and a standalone hash walk) were consolidated into `analyze_bool_cache()`. Temporal `FilterValue::Temporal` constants are also no longer hashed via debug formatting; `hash_flake_value()` now hashes temporal and duration variants using their stable `original()` lexical forms, with structural hashing for other `FlakeValue` variants." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "expression" ;
    mem:tag "hashing" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "temporal" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/conditional.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs" ;
    mem:supersedes mem:fact-01kmtec88erhp5fk1f4gfybyp0 ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T14:48:59.155982+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmtf7e63dh83atzzsr92t8bx a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Boolean expression caching now has a prepared form for hot filter paths. `fluree-db-query/src/expression/helpers.rs` defines `PreparedBoolExpression`, which precomputes the optional cache spec once from an `Expression` and then reuses it across row evaluations. The main repeated filter-bearing operator paths now construct prepared expressions at build time: `FilterOperator`, `HavingOperator`, `InlineOperator::Filter`, and `BindOperator`'s fused post-bind filters. Generic `Expression::eval_to_bool()` still supports uncached ad hoc use, but hot query execution paths no longer re-run cacheability analysis on every row." ;
    mem:tag "cache" ;
    mem:tag "expression" ;
    mem:tag "filter" ;
    mem:tag "operator" ;
    mem:tag "performance" ;
    mem:tag "prepared" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
