mem:fact-01kmtgrqzhejen89tyr9046wq0 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Several JSON-LD/UNION API integration tests in `fluree-db-api` were relying on implicit row order without `orderBy`. After query planner/executor changes, the result sets were still semantically correct but row order shifted, so `it_query_jsonld::jsonld_filter_filtering_for_absence` and `it_query_misc::{union_basic_combine_emails, union_passthrough_variables}` needed order-insensitive assertions (`sort()` or `normalize_rows`) instead of raw `assert_eq!` on unsorted rows. `union_different_variables` was updated similarly for consistency." ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "ordering" ;
    mem:tag "regression" ;
    mem:tag "tests" ;
    mem:tag "union" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_jsonld.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_misc.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T15:24:56.689659+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .

mem:fact-01kmth3vjk05yrpfpmcjq5nfjz a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "LocalStack testcontainers tests in `fluree-db-connection/tests/aws_testcontainers_test.rs` can intermittently fail under `cargo nextest` with `PortNotExposed { port: Tcp(4566) }` immediately after `image.start().await`, even though plain `cargo test` passes. A reliable fix is to centralize LocalStack startup and retry `container.get_host_port_ipv4(4566)` for a short window before treating startup as failed." ;
    mem:tag "aws-testcontainers" ;
    mem:tag "flaky-tests" ;
    mem:tag "localstack" ;
    mem:tag "nextest" ;
    mem:tag "port-mapping" ;
    mem:tag "testcontainers" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-connection/tests/aws_testcontainers_test.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-03-28T15:31:00.819186+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "configuration" .

mem:fact-01kn6wpk6vgvv0hh2nrz9fczbt a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "cargo-dist 0.31.0 plan for the current release setup produces app/artifact names based on the package name `fluree-db-cli`: shell installer `fluree-db-cli-installer.sh`, PowerShell installer `fluree-db-cli-installer.ps1`, Homebrew formula/install hint `brew install fluree/tap/fluree-db-cli`, and Linux/macOS archives named `fluree-db-cli-<target>.tar.xz` (not simplified `fluree-*` names and not `.tar.gz`). Any docs or Docker extraction steps should match those exact names/extensions unless dist metadata is changed to rename the app/formula." ;
    mem:tag "artifact-names" ;
    mem:tag "cargo-dist" ;
    mem:tag "docker" ;
    mem:tag "fluree-db-cli" ;
    mem:tag "homebrew" ;
    mem:tag "installer" ;
    mem:tag "release" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "internal" ;
    mem:artifactRef ".github/workflows/release.yml" ;
    mem:artifactRef "dist-workspace.toml" ;
