mem:fact-01knymjwzpn6s9rysnwv6hcd0j a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "SPARQL SERVICE parser now wired (step 1 of federation rollout).\n\n`fluree-db-sparql` parses `SERVICE [SILENT] <iri>|?var { ... }` via `parse_service_pattern()` in `fluree-db-sparql/src/parse/query/pattern.rs`, dispatched from `parse_group_graph_pattern` on `TokenKind::KwService`.\n\nNo IR changes needed — AST `GraphPattern::Service`, lowering `lower_service_pattern`, and `ServiceOperator` were already in place. Parser unit tests in `parse/query/tests.rs` cover IRI/var/prefixed endpoints, SILENT, mixed-group, and error paths. End-to-end tests in `fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_sparql.rs`:\n- Self-reference `fluree:ledger:<alias>` executes against the current ledger (works via service.rs fallback: when no dataset is attached, `ctx.snapshot.ledger_id` equality check).\n- External `https://...` endpoint errors cleanly without SILENT.\n- External endpoint + SERVICE SILENT swallows the error and yields zero rows.\n\nExternal (non-Fluree) endpoints still error with `QueryError::InvalidQuery` at fluree-db-query/src/service.rs:360-373 — step 2 (bound-join remote execution) replaces that branch.\n\nGotcha: the parent tree `/Users/bplatz/fluree/db-r` and the worktree `.claude/worktrees/frosty-shirley` have separate copies of each crate. Always edit files via the worktree absolute path when cargo is running from the worktree, otherwise edits silently don't take effect." ;
    mem:tag "SERVICE" ;
    mem:tag "SPARQL" ;
    mem:tag "federation" ;
    mem:tag "parser" ;
    mem:tag "step-1" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-api/tests/it_query_sparql.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/service.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/parse/query/pattern.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-sparql/src/parse/query/tests.rs" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-11T16:04:19.062797+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp44ka6rpf7qd2ddpq65mywd a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Strict compact-IRI guard implemented for JSON-LD parsing surfaces.\n\nWhat: Unresolved compact-looking IRIs (e.g. ex:Person when ex is not in @context) are rejected at parse time on JSON-LD boundaries. The guard uses a single split_once(':') plus a small allowlist of known schemes.\n\nWhere the guard lives:\n- Shared helper: fluree-graph-json-ld/src/iri.rs — check_unresolved_iri() and UnresolvedIriDisposition enum\n- Checked expansion fns: expand::details_checked(), expand::iri_checked(), expand::node_checked()\n- Public API: expand_iri_checked(), details_checked(), details_with_vocab_checked(), expand_with_context_checked()\n\nWhere it's wired in (JSON-LD boundaries only):\n- Query parser (fluree-db-query/src/parse/): node_map.rs, mod.rs, path_expr.rs, values.rs — all use details_checked / expand_iri_checked\n- Transaction expansion (fluree-db-transact/src/parse/jsonld.rs): uses expand_with_context_checked for JSON-LD expansion pass, and details_checked at specific IRI positions\n- Transaction datatype IRI: expand_datatype_iri() has builtin xsd:/rdf: fallbacks, only applies guard after all fallbacks fail\n\nNOT wired into (by design):\n- Generic expand() / expand_with_context() — remain permissive (used by connection-config parsing etc.)\n- Heuristic \"looks like IRI\" detection in transact parser — use unchecked details() since they have fallback to literal strings\n- SPARQL / Turtle / other syntaxes\n\nKnown scheme allowlist: urn, did, mailto, tel, data, ipfs, ipns, geo, blob, magnet, fluree. Compared case-insensitively.\n\nThe strict flag pattern: expand_node_internal and helpers accept strict: bool. node() passes false (permissive default), node_checked() passes true." ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:branch "misc/fixes" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-13T19:20:21.976979+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

mem:fact-01kp4g1wa8yyty4sd2p03k6bg9 a mem:Fact ;
    mem:content "Strict compact-IRI opt-out wiring has two easy-to-miss edge cases: (1) JSON-LD query `@path` alias extraction currently happens before parse-policy resolution, so `opts.strictCompactIri:false` will not relax undefined-prefix checks inside `@context` `@path` expressions; (2) JSON-LD transaction parse-time `opts` must be stripped before single-object insert/upsert expansion, otherwise `opts` can be treated as normal data because only top-level envelope `@graph` form skips extra keys before expansion." ;
    mem:tag "jsonld" ;
    mem:tag "opts" ;
    mem:tag "path-alias" ;
    mem:tag "query" ;
    mem:tag "strict-compact-iri" ;
    mem:tag "transaction" ;
    mem:scope mem:repo ;
    mem:sensitivity "public" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/mod.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-query/src/parse/policy.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-db-transact/src/parse/jsonld.rs" ;
    mem:artifactRef "fluree-graph-json-ld/src/expand.rs" ;
    mem:createdAt "2026-04-13T22:40:33.608461+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    mem:factKind "architecture" .
